            <title><![CDATA[Indiana Jones, Marvel Rivals, Secret Level, And More Of The Week's Reviews]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/indiana-jones-great-circle-review-marvel-rivals-1851720877</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/indiana-jones-marvel-rivals-secret-level-and-more-of-the-weeks-reviews.1061718/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/indiana-jones-great-circle-review-marvel-rivals-1851720877<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="05cf438face92daa843691d53cc87bf1" data-recommend-id="image://05cf438face92daa843691d53cc87bf1" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Chrispecoraro<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)<!-- -->, <!-- -->Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Bethesda / Lucasfilm / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Amazon / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Square Enix / Vanillaware / Microbird Games / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="05cf438face92daa843691d53cc87bf1" data-recommend-id="image://05cf438face92daa843691d53cc87bf1" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The long-anticipated <em>Indiana Jones and the Great Circle </em>has finally arrived, and it’s different—and better—that what we expected, really putting you in the boots of Harrison Ford’s adventurous archaeologist to become something of an Indiana Jones simulator. Read our full review for lots more on this terrific new release, and while you’re here, also check out our takes on Amazon’s animated anthology series <em>Secret Level</em> and the hot new <em>Overwatch </em>competitor <em>Marvel Rivals, </em>as well as our picks for the best RPGs of 2024. </p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="a93dd2a5b206e805e3ab22840d1b129a" data-recommend-id="image://a93dd2a5b206e805e3ab22840d1b129a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows kids tossing popcorn in a movie theater. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image shows kids tossing popcorn in a movie theater. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="getty" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Photo<!-- -->: <!-- -->Chrispecoraro<!-- --> (<!-- -->Getty Images<!-- -->)</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="a93dd2a5b206e805e3ab22840d1b129a" data-recommend-id="image://a93dd2a5b206e805e3ab22840d1b129a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image shows kids tossing popcorn in a movie theater. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>2024 has been a solid, if somewhat strange year for movies. This year saw the release of some great films across both streaming platforms and in theaters.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/worst-movies-2024-metacritic-madame-web-borderlands-1851718062&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/worst-movies-2024-metacritic-madame-web-borderlands-1851718062">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="db44c530c1e5ce803810c8d30a4f3f96" data-recommend-id="image://db44c530c1e5ce803810c8d30a4f3f96" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An screenshot shows Indy as seen in the game. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An screenshot shows Indy as seen in the game. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Bethesda / Lucasfilm / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="db44c530c1e5ce803810c8d30a4f3f96" data-recommend-id="image://db44c530c1e5ce803810c8d30a4f3f96" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An screenshot shows Indy as seen in the game. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/how-long-is-indiana-jones-great-circle-xbox-game-pass-1851708781&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/how-long-is-indiana-jones-great-circle-xbox-game-pass-1851708781"><em>Indiana Jones and the Great Circle</em></a></span> is not what I was expecting. My expectation and fear was that developer MachineGames’ AAA action-adventure adaptation of the popular franchise starring Harrison Ford would play mostly like <em>Uncharted</em>, but in the ‘30s and with more Nazis. Thankfully, <em>Great Circle</em> is nothing like <em>Tomb Raider</em>, <em>Uncharted</em>, or the countless other games that have been directly inspired by Spielberg’s iconic ‘80s adventure films. Instead, <em>Great Circle</em> mixes <em>Hitman</em>-like stealth, <em>Dishonored</em>-like first-person gameplay, and some escape room puzzle design to create a unique, open-ended experience that feels both fresh and yet distinctly like Indiana Jones. - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/indiana-jones-great-circle-review-is-it-good-pc-xbox-1851717174&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/indiana-jones-great-circle-review-is-it-good-pc-xbox-1851717174">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="ec57c7ab74aadacd08df413b08e3da86" data-recommend-id="image://ec57c7ab74aadacd08df413b08e3da86" data-format="jpg" data-width="1411" data-height="794" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Kratos stands on a city street." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Kratos stands on a city street." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Amazon / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="ec57c7ab74aadacd08df413b08e3da86" data-recommend-id="image://ec57c7ab74aadacd08df413b08e3da86" data-format="jpg" data-width="1411" data-height="794" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Kratos stands on a city street." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[]" href="https://www.amazon.com/salp/secretlevel?asc_campaign=kinjakotakulink-20&amp;asc_refurl=https://kotaku.com/indiana-jones-great-circle-review-marvel-rivals-1851720877&amp;asc_source=&amp;tag=kinjakotakulink-20" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer nofollow noskim" data-vtas-click="self:InlineUrl:inline-url-postbody" data-amazonasin="" data-amazontag="kinjakotakulink-20"><em>Secret Level</em></a></span>, Amazon’s stunningly animated video game anthology tribute, is either a gorgeous, impactful vehicle through which some short stories are told or a soulless piece of capital C Content, depending on which episode you’re watching. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/secret-level-review-amazon-playstation-pac-man-mega-man-1851716804&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/secret-level-review-amazon-playstation-pac-man-mega-man-1851716804">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2229f739dad206bb6bc81ddf5168ee54" data-recommend-id="image://2229f739dad206bb6bc81ddf5168ee54" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Art shows the top RPGs of 2024. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Art shows the top RPGs of 2024. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Square Enix / Vanillaware / Microbird Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2229f739dad206bb6bc81ddf5168ee54" data-recommend-id="image://2229f739dad206bb6bc81ddf5168ee54" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Art shows the top RPGs of 2024. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>We’re living through a role-playing game renaissance right now. The <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/the-best-rpgs-of-2021-1848257887&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/the-best-rpgs-of-2021-1848257887">last</a></span> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/best-rpgs-2022-pokemon-arceus-elden-ring-final-fantasy-1849893161&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/best-rpgs-2022-pokemon-arceus-elden-ring-final-fantasy-1849893161">several</a></span> <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/best-rpgs-2023-jrpg-baldur-s-gate-3-octopath-traveler-2-1851128706&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/best-rpgs-2023-jrpg-baldur-s-gate-3-octopath-traveler-2-1851128706">years</a></span> have been full of great ones, and 2024 is no different. Everywhere you look the genre is growing, evolving, and dominating. From Japanese-style RPGs to Western-style ones, retro remakes to open-world sequels, there’s never been more to dig into for fans of exploration, branching dialogue, or just making the numbers go up. - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/2024-best-rpgs-this-year-ff7-dragon-age-4-elden-ring-1851717064&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/2024-best-rpgs-this-year-ff7-dragon-age-4-elden-ring-1851717064">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="9bcda5c666c54398129711fe5fccf59a" data-recommend-id="image://9bcda5c666c54398129711fe5fccf59a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9bcda5c666c54398129711fe5fccf59a" data-recommend-id="image://9bcda5c666c54398129711fe5fccf59a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Marvel Rivals</em>, NetEase’s <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-beta-impressions-preview-overwatch-1851610920&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-beta-impressions-preview-overwatch-1851610920">shameless <em>Overwatch</em>-like</a></span> featuring the heroes and villains that have captivated comic book readers and moviegoers for decades, is already at a crossroads. It’s less than a week old, but it’s clear even now that the decisions NetEase makes in the coming months will determine if it stays a chaotic, unbalanced blast or if it joins the ranks of its hero shooter contemporaries as a polished, esports-ready sweatfest that only appeals to a fraction of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://x.com/MarvelRivals/status/1865909229070016851&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://x.com/MarvelRivals/status/1865909229070016851" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">its huge fanbase</a></span>. I’ve spent years poring over Blizzard’s <em>Overwatch </em>patch notes, watching content creators nitpick every tiny tweak to damage output and suffering <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-sombra-season-13-patch-notes-ramattra-1851673081&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/overwatch-2-sombra-season-13-patch-notes-ramattra-1851673081">the loss of some of the most interesting shooter kits</a></span> I’ve ever used because someone cried foul at abilities they believed “unfair.” I don’t know what <em>Marvel Rivals </em>will be in a year, so I recommend you play it now before the team behind it has a chance to sand down the things that make it fun. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-review-hero-shooter-overwatch-netease-1851717975">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Everything We Saw At The 2024 Game Awards And More Of The Week's Top Stories]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-reveals-announcements-witcher-4-1851720875</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/everything-we-saw-at-the-2024-game-awards-and-more-of-the-weeks-top-stories.1061658/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-reveals-announcements-witcher-4-1851720875<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="96eeb75fe84691f5675cae446bcb6f65" data-recommend-id="image://96eeb75fe84691f5675cae446bcb6f65" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="in-house-art" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Naughty Dog<!-- -->, <!-- -->Marvel / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->The Game Awards / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->2K Games / X / mnm345x / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Naughty Dog / Sony / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Activision<!-- -->, <!-- -->FromSoftware / Bandai Namco<!-- -->, <!-- -->Game Awards / Sony / Square Enix / PlayStack / Kotaku<!-- -->, <!-- -->Arrowhead Studios<!-- -->, <!-- -->Epic Games / Lego</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="96eeb75fe84691f5675cae446bcb6f65" data-recommend-id="image://96eeb75fe84691f5675cae446bcb6f65" data-format="jpg" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The 2024 Game Awards were held this past Thursday and unsurprisingly, the reveals that occurred at&nbsp;Geoff Keighley’s big show dwarfed most other happenings in the world of games this week. In addition to our exhaustive breakdown of everything revealed at this year’s event, we’ve got closer looks at <em>The Witcher 4</em>, <em>Mafia: The Old Country</em>, <em>Intergalactic: The Heretic Prophet</em>, and more.&nbsp;</p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-recommend-id="image://f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The main character of Intergalactic sips a drink through a straw. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="The main character of Intergalactic sips a drink through a straw. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Naughty Dog</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-recommend-id="image://f4ee1ae43b2f693ec6270e5c262a7f44" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="The main character of Intergalactic sips a drink through a straw. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>It’s that time of year when the video game industry gathers in Los Angeles to hear Geoff Keighley talk about what a good year it was, whether that’s actually true or not. But as we reflect on the last 12 months, we also get several trailers for games that are coming out in the future. If you weren’t able to catch the show and just want the highlights of what world premieres were there, here’s a rundown of every trailer and announcement made during The Game Awards 2024. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-trailers-announcements-world-premieres-1851720032&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-trailers-announcements-world-premieres-1851720032">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="82bd3d953746625eed6b7d686dc784cf" data-recommend-id="image://82bd3d953746625eed6b7d686dc784cf" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Jeff looks at the camera." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Jeff looks at the camera." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Marvel / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="82bd3d953746625eed6b7d686dc784cf" data-recommend-id="image://82bd3d953746625eed6b7d686dc784cf" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Jeff looks at the camera." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-tips-team-up-currency-battle-pass-heroes-1851715661&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-tips-team-up-currency-battle-pass-heroes-1851715661"><em>Marvel Rivals</em></a></span><em> </em>launched last week, and as fans are flocking to the game <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://x.com/MarvelRivals/status/1865909229070016851&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://x.com/MarvelRivals/status/1865909229070016851" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">in droves</a></span>, they’re also figuring out who their favorite and least favorite characters are on the hero shooter’s roster. Right now, the game feels like it’s in the pre-patch state of just <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-beta-impressions-preview-overwatch-1851610920&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-beta-impressions-preview-overwatch-1851610920">being a real chaotic shooter</a></span> that hasn’t yet been sanded down by months of balance patches. Currently, few characters are as chaotic as Jeff the Land Shark, the strategist hero who is, at a glance, just a silly little guy. However, as <em>Marvel Rivals </em>players have learned, this happy dude is actually one of the biggest menaces in the game, and god, I hope NetEase keeps him like this forever. - Kenneth Shepard <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-jeff-the-land-shark-ultimate-ability-1851716962&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/marvel-rivals-jeff-the-land-shark-ultimate-ability-1851716962">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="6c2d20a36e6ebbea591c93d755c13b09" data-recommend-id="image://6c2d20a36e6ebbea591c93d755c13b09" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of a shark-man hybrid seen in Black Ops 6. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="An image of a shark-man hybrid seen in Black Ops 6. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Activision</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="6c2d20a36e6ebbea591c93d755c13b09" data-recommend-id="image://6c2d20a36e6ebbea591c93d755c13b09" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="An image of a shark-man hybrid seen in Black Ops 6. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Black Ops 6,</em> the latest entry in the <em>Call of Duty </em>series, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nicki-minaj-barbie-call-of-duty-skin-price-how-much-1850775467&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nicki-minaj-barbie-call-of-duty-skin-price-how-much-1850775467">contains some really bizarre and wacky cosmetics</a></span>. And while some players hate them, it doesn’t seem like the developers behind the game are going to stop making them any time soon.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/black-ops-call-of-duty-wacky-weird-skins-dev-explains-1851719188&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/black-ops-call-of-duty-wacky-weird-skins-dev-explains-1851719188">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="c1e0cac78f1bf8121658a00e3dbefe6c" data-recommend-id="image://c1e0cac78f1bf8121658a00e3dbefe6c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Ciri appears in a village. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Ciri appears in a village. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->The Game Awards / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c1e0cac78f1bf8121658a00e3dbefe6c" data-recommend-id="image://c1e0cac78f1bf8121658a00e3dbefe6c" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Ciri appears in a village. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>We finally have our first taste of <em>The Witcher 4</em> and it looks stunning in a new cinematic trailer that aired at The Game Awards 2024. The cinematic tease showed monster hunter Ciri stepping into mentor Geralt of Rivia’s shoes to take on a gnarly-looking beast in proper witcher fashion.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/witcher-4-cdpr-ciri-open-world-rpg-release-date-trailer-1851720322&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/witcher-4-cdpr-ciri-open-world-rpg-release-date-trailer-1851720322">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="2c2eea83e816542f58cdcc1bd0d03388" data-recommend-id="image://2c2eea83e816542f58cdcc1bd0d03388" data-format="jpg" data-width="1403" data-height="789" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A warrior stands on a battlefield." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A warrior stands on a battlefield." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->FromSoftware / Bandai Namco</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="2c2eea83e816542f58cdcc1bd0d03388" data-recommend-id="image://2c2eea83e816542f58cdcc1bd0d03388" data-format="jpg" data-width="1403" data-height="789" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A warrior stands on a battlefield." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>FromSoftware <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-shadow-of-the-erdtree-dlc-expansion-review-1851545505&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-shadow-of-the-erdtree-dlc-expansion-review-1851545505">isn’t done with <em>Elden Ring</em> yet</a></span>. The hit open-world RPG that just got a GOTY-nominated expansion is coming back with a completely new spin-off in 2025. It’s called <em>Elden Ring: Nightreign </em>and it’s a co-op action adventure that looks as excellent as the game it’s based on.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-multiplayer-release-date-trailer-1851720335&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/elden-ring-nightreign-multiplayer-release-date-trailer-1851720335">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="f2e692df85c6fc0a2b4884b670e8f7db" data-recommend-id="image://f2e692df85c6fc0a2b4884b670e8f7db" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Game Awards / Sony / Square Enix / PlayStack / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f2e692df85c6fc0a2b4884b670e8f7db" data-recommend-id="image://f2e692df85c6fc0a2b4884b670e8f7db" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>And so, another Game Awards is done. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/game-awards-keighley-e3-trailers-1851083267?_gl=1*8faphd*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNDA0NjUzMS45OC4xLjE3MzQwNDgxNjMuMTkuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/game-awards-keighley-e3-trailers-1851083267?_gl=1*8faphd*_ga*NzE0NzM5NTc5LjE3Mjk4Njg5MzU.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNDA0NjUzMS45OC4xLjE3MzQwNDgxNjMuMTkuMC4w">Geoff Keighley’s annual trailer-a-thon</a></span> once again included some game awards shoved in between all the ads and teasers and more ads. If you want to know who won what (and who lost), we’ve got you covered. - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-rebirth-astro-bot-winners-goty-list-1851720291&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-rebirth-astro-bot-winners-goty-list-1851720291">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="9656e2ddcd11d25fcab9b8e7bf69f098" data-recommend-id="image://9656e2ddcd11d25fcab9b8e7bf69f098" data-format="png" data-width="1043" data-height="587" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man looks out the window as light reflects off his eyes. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A man looks out the window as light reflects off his eyes. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->2K Games / X / mnm345x / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9656e2ddcd11d25fcab9b8e7bf69f098" data-recommend-id="image://9656e2ddcd11d25fcab9b8e7bf69f098" data-format="png" data-width="1043" data-height="587" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man looks out the window as light reflects off his eyes. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The fourth entry in <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mafia-series-2-3-sale-hangar-13-new-game-1851628204&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mafia-series-2-3-sale-hangar-13-new-game-1851628204">2K’s gangster series</a></span> isn’t far away. A new leaked ad for <em>Mafia: The Old Country</em> ahead of <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/game-awards-elden-ring-dlc-goty-dragon-age-tga-2024-1851702305?_gl=1*1hx67qv*_ga*ODE3ODM5ODIyLjE3MjA0NjY0NTg.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNDAxMjEwOC40Ny4xLjE3MzQwMTM5ODguNjAuMC4w&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/game-awards-elden-ring-dlc-goty-dragon-age-tga-2024-1851702305?_gl=1*1hx67qv*_ga*ODE3ODM5ODIyLjE3MjA0NjY0NTg.*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNDAxMjEwOC40Ny4xLjE3MzQwMTM5ODguNjAuMC4w">The Game Awards 2024</a></span> reveals a summer 2025 release window and our first real look at the upcoming prequel.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/mafia-4-gta-6-trailer-release-date-game-awards-2024-1851719492&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/mafia-4-gta-6-trailer-release-date-game-awards-2024-1851719492">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="0d0b485623d76095b6db47fe6a99ea7f" data-recommend-id="image://0d0b485623d76095b6db47fe6a99ea7f" data-format="jpg" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Helldivers ride in a vehicle. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Helldivers ride in a vehicle. " data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Arrowhead Studios</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="0d0b485623d76095b6db47fe6a99ea7f" data-recommend-id="image://0d0b485623d76095b6db47fe6a99ea7f" data-format="jpg" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Helldivers ride in a vehicle. " data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p><em>Helldivers 2</em> fans have been waiting patiently (and not so patiently) for the alien horde shooter to add a new enemy faction, and Arrowhead Studios is finally doing just that. The Illuminate are now live in the game following a surprise free update called Omens of Tyranny, and it adds a ton more than just the series’ infamous blue aquatic aliens.  - Ethan Gach <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-illuminate-omens-tyranny-free-update-1851720355&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-illuminate-omens-tyranny-free-update-1851720355">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="290408f18d399179c68cdeae4658ce59" data-recommend-id="image://290408f18d399179c68cdeae4658ce59" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Naughty Dog / Sony / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="290408f18d399179c68cdeae4658ce59" data-recommend-id="image://290408f18d399179c68cdeae4658ce59" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>The Game Awards ended with a big finale, a new trailer revealing Naughty Dog’s next game. It’s called <em>Intergalactic: The Heretic Prophet </em> and it looks really, really cool and stylish, mixing lo-fi tech and sci-fi bounty hunters. - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/naughty-dog-last-of-us-intergalatic-trailer-game-awards-1851720381&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/naughty-dog-last-of-us-intergalatic-trailer-game-awards-1851720381">Read More</a></span></p></div><div><figure id="" data-id="bba7ca3428332036b19b56203aff4fa3" data-recommend-id="image://bba7ca3428332036b19b56203aff4fa3" data-format="jpg" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Epic Games / Lego</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="bba7ca3428332036b19b56203aff4fa3" data-recommend-id="image://bba7ca3428332036b19b56203aff4fa3" data-format="jpg" data-width="3840" data-height="2160" data-lightbox="false" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Later this week, Epic will release <em>Lego Brick Life</em>, a <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gta-6-grand-theft-auto-vi-first-trailer-2-a-year-later-1851714995&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gta-6-grand-theft-auto-vi-first-trailer-2-a-year-later-1851714995"><em>GTA</em></a></span>-inspired roleplaying game that will be playable in <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/how-parents-can-get-started-in-fortnite-1851688072&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/how-parents-can-get-started-in-fortnite-1851688072"><em>Fortnite</em></a></span><em>. Brick Life</em> will let you and up to 20+ other players hang out, earn money, buy a home, and party together.  - Zack Zwiezen <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gta-6-lego-fortnite-brick-life-roleplay-ps5-xbox-pc-1851716667&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gta-6-lego-fortnite-brick-life-roleplay-ps5-xbox-pc-1851716667">Read More</a></span></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
